<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 5000, 9000 Series Without Lowered heater Box - COMPONENTS - HEATER WATER
        VALVE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>HEATER WATER VALVE</title>
        <para>The heater water valve (heater shut off) is attached to the frame of the Blend-Air duct door (
            <hotlnk document="s16015_5.xml" xrefid="f1601505">Figure 5</hotlnk>). The inlet hose is connected to it, and
            the valve meters the flow of hot engine coolant through the core. The valve is operated by an adjustable
            link connecting the valve to the Blend-Air door, which is controlled by the cable connected to the control
            panel HTR lever.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
